Peru Stocks: Buenaventura Falls; Credicorp, Relapasa, Maple Gain

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-10-18T21:44:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/peru-stocks-buenaventura-falls-credicorp-relapasa-maple-gain.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the close of trading.  The Lima General Index gained 1.4 percent to 18,988.64. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose 1.2 percent to 2,487.28.  Banks and energy companies climbed as U.S. stocks surged
after the Guardian reported Germany and  France  will boost the
size of the euro region’s rescue fund for indebted states.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, jumped the most in three
months, rising 6 percent to $1.06. Refineria La Pampilla SA
(RELAPAC1 PE), the country’s largest petroleum refinery known as
Relapasa, rose 3.8 percent to 82 centimos.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services company, rose 2.4 percent
to a six-month high of $105.50. BBVA Banco Continental SA
(CONTINC1 PE), the local unit of  Spain ’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya
Argentaria SA, advanced 3.3 percent to 5.70 soles.  Gold producers fell as the metal declined in  New York  after
a stronger dollar reduced demand for an alternative asset.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, fell 1.9 percent to $39.83, a
one-week low.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper
and gold exploration company, dropped 2.3 percent to 42 cents.
 Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration
company, declined 1.5 percent to $2.58.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
